<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Filatov: `Economic Policy of Compromise' To Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Filatov: `Economic Policy of Compromise' To Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1206095894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0934 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1206095894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Aleksandrova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 12 TASS -- "An economic policy of 
compromise pursued by the Russian Government which was commented 
upon by the leader of Russia's Choice movement, Yegor Gaydar at 
the opening of the Russia's Choice founding congress today, will 
be continued for some time until the situation in society 
stabilises," said Presidential Chief of Staff Sergey Filatov, 
who is a delegate to the congress. 
  "After the situation stabilizes, after regions give their 
full support, it will be possible to take more resolute and 
tough steps," he said. He pointed out that the course of 
resolving problems by the president's decrees will be continued. 
  In reply to a question asked by ITAR-TASS, Filatov pointed 
out that he is a delegate of the congress and was one of the 
party's organisers at the first stage of its creation. But it's 
too early to speak about membership in the party yet, since 
practically, it has not yet been created, he said. 
  According to Filatov, the president did not express his 
attitude to the newly created party on the eve of its founding 
congress. 

</TEXT>

