<H3> <TI>   Grachev Says 300,000 Troops To Be Cut by Oct </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Grachev Says 300,000 Troops To Be Cut by Oct </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306095694 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 
13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1306095694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The authorized strength of the Russian Armed Forces 
would be 1.9 million by 1 October 1994, Russian Defense Minister 
Pavel Grachev told Interfax. 
  At present, the authorized strength of the Russian Armed 
Forces is 2.2 million. 
  Grachev noted that it was not only the rank-and-file and 
officer corps which were to be cut -- general officers were to 
be cut, too. He said that 270 generals' posts would be cut by 
the end of the year. 

</TEXT>

