<H3> <TI>   Smolensk Nuclear Plant Reportedly Undamaged After Flood </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Smolensk Nuclear Plant Reportedly Undamaged After Flood </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1206122794 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1100 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1206122794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Our special correspondent Dmitriy Motrich reported 
over the phone from Smolensk today that a natural disaster had 
occurred last night in Smolensk Oblast, not far from the town of 
Roslavl, the site of the Smolensk nuclear power station. 
Torrential rains broke a dam, houses were flooded, and farms 
destroyed. The area has lost its electricity and communications 
lines. The number of victims is still unclear. 
  According to preliminary reports, the nuclear power station 
itself is unharmed. Our correspondents have already arrived at 
the site, and we will keep you posted. 

</TEXT>

