<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military, Nuclear &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cosmonauts Complete 5 Months Aboard Mir Space Complex </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cosmonauts Complete 5 Months Aboard Mir Space Complex </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006112594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0923 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1006112594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By unidentified ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Mission Control Centre June 10 TASS -- Russian 
cosmonauts Viktor Afanasyev, Yuriy Usachev, and Valeriy Polyakov 
have spent five months on board the "Mir" complex. 
  They devoted primary attention to geophysical studies this 
week, which were carried out with the help of a multizonal 
MKF-6MA camera and videospectrometric equipment, installed on 
the "Kvant-2" module. Today, the cosmonauts are to make a 
regular series of photographs of the earth's surface. They will 
also carry out several experiments to determine the spectral 
characteristics of major oceanic currents and to further study 
the ionosphere and the earth's magnetosphere. 
  Astrophysical studies were carried out regularly in recent 
days with the use of the international "roentgen" orbital 
observatory. The telescopes were trained on the centre of our 
galaxy, at the roentgen pulsar, the power of whose radiation 
grew approximately 10-fold at the beginning of May. 
  Medical examinations show that the cosmonauts are in good 
health. The flight is proceeding normally. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

