<H3> <TI>   Meshkov Approves Crimean State Affairs Service Regulations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meshkov Approves Crimean State Affairs Service Regulations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1106183894 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 1500 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1106183894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Simferopol, 11 June -- Crimean President Yuriy 
Meshkov issued instructions approving the regulations of the 
state affairs service of the Republic of Crimea. In compliance 
with these regulations the service consists of the directorate 
for the affairs of the Crimean president, the directorate for 
the affairs of the Crimean Government, the protocol department, 
the legal service, the information and analysis service, the 
service for the research of foreign political issues, and the 
financial service. The service will have 123 people on staff. 

</TEXT>

