<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Plushch Says Kiev `May Soon Be' Leading Arms Exporter </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Plushch Says Kiev `May Soon Be' Leading Arms Exporter </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1206150094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1441 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1206150094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ukraine may soon be a leading exporter of its most 
sophisticated weapons, says the report by the analytical center 
of the election team of the candidate for presidency Ivan 
Plushch, which was released in Kiev on Sunday [12 June]. 
  The document says the most promising export item may be the 
Kharkov-produced tank T-84 which surpasses in performance 
characteristics, western tanks and the Russian one, T-80. 
  Experts believe that Ukrainian submarines, air defence 
missile systems and missile complexes for Navy have good export 
characteristics. 
  Analysts believe, in 1995 Ukraine plans to start the 
production of a new submachine gun on the basis of the 
Kalashnikov. It surpasses the base model by many parameters. 
  The document says that Asia may be the most promising market 
for Ukrainian armaments. In this respect, Ukraine may be 
interested in the proposal by the Indian company, Resources 
Argumentation, which is prepared to give Ukraine a long-term 
credit for the development of the Ukrainian industry. 

</TEXT>

