<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Voters Back Kravchuk in Poll of Presidential Candidates </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Voters Back Kravchuk in Poll of Presidential Candidates </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006155094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1354 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1006155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko, </F>
Mikhail Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev 10 June TASS -- Over 27 per cent of voters 
would like Leonid Kravchuk to become Ukrainian president again. 
Ex-Premier Leonid Kuchma is supported by 20 per cent of voters, 
the second rating. Speaker of the Ukrainian Parliament 
Aleksandr Morozov is third, being backed by eleven per cent of 
voters. The fourth and fifth places are held by Vladimir 
Lanovoy, a prominent Ukrainian economist favouring the market, 
and Ivan Plyushch, former chairman of the Supreme Soviet. They 
are backed by four to 6 per cent of voters. Entrepreneur 
Valeriy Babich and Education Minister Petr Palanchuk are 
supported by only one per cent of voters. 
  This information was supplied to ITAR-TASS by the Kiev 
International Institute of Sociology and the sociology chair of 
the Kiev-Mogilyanskiy Academy which conducted a selective 
representative survey in Ukraine. As many as 1,004 people were 
polled in 126 cities and villages in 24 regions of Ukraine and 
the Republic of Crimea. 
  There is information that 73 per cent of voters now intend 
to 
participate in the elections. Ten per cent are yet undecided. 
17 per cent will not vote. 
  The poll also showed that Leonid Kravchuk is supported 
mostly 
by Ukrainian population, while Leonid Kuchma is supported by 
Russian-speaking population. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

