<H3> <TI>   Nova Khvylya Members To Support Kravchuk </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nova Khvylya Members To Support Kravchuk </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS1006141394 Lvov POST-INFORM in Ukrainian 1200 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1006141394 </F>
<F P=104>  Lvov POST-INFORM </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 8 June at a news conference held in Lvov, 
Oleksandr Yemets, minister for issues of nationalities and 
immigration (who is running in the Supreme Council elections in 
Lvov's Halytskyy constituency supported by the "Nova Khvylya" 
coalition) addressed the issue of presidential elections. 
  Oleksandr Yemets said that candidates whom he would like to 
support (for example, Lanovyy), unfortunately, do not have any 
chances. The only possible competition is the one between 
Kravchuk and Kuchma. The nationalities minister stated that he 
is ready to support any candidate capable of countering Kuchma. 
"Although I have a great number of critical remarks regarding 
Kravchuk, the current situation is that no one but he can do 
that," Oleksandr Yemets said. 
  The same position was voiced last week by People's Deputy 
Taras Stetskiv, one of the "Nova Khvylya" leaders, in an 
interview with VYSOKYY ZAMOK. 

</TEXT>

