<H3> <TI>   Contaminated Water Leakage `Inconsiderable' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Contaminated Water Leakage `Inconsiderable' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006175894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1702 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1006175894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko, </F>
Mikhail Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev 10 June TASS -- An inconsiderable increase of 
technological leakage of contaminated water from the Chernobyl 
nuclear power plant's basin of worked-out fuel assemblies has 
been registered today, head of the Ukrainian State Committee for 
Nuclear Power Engineering's Emergency-Dispatcher Department 
Sergey Nazarenko told ITAR-TASS. 
  In his words, the system of technological water collection 
excludes their leakage in the environment and provides for 
reliable collection of the contaminated water and its processing. 
  The radiation situation at the Chernobyl nuclear power plant 
is now normal, he said. 

</TEXT>

