<H3> <TI>   Another Water Leak Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Another Water Leak Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1106220894 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 2105 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1106220894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] On 11 June a water leak was discovered at the 
Chernobyl nuclear power station in Ukraine. The water was 
leaking from the holding reservoir of the power generating unit 
No. 2. The reservoir is used to store cassettes with worked-out 
fuel. A shift leader at the Chernobyl nuclear power station, 
Aleksandr Yelchishchev, said the leak had not led to changes in 
background radiation levels in the nearby premises. Let me 
remind you that in accordance with the existing schedule, power 
generating unit No. 2 is currently undergoing decommissioning. 

</TEXT>

