<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Saeima Adopts Citizenship Bill </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Saeima Adopts Citizenship Bill </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906194294 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1700 GMT 9 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0906194294 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>
<F P=105>  Latvian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today a plenary session of the Saeima adopted at its 
second reading the Latvian citizenship bill. The bill 
determines that Latvian citizens are persons who were Latvian 
citizens on 17 June 1940, as well as those persons' descendants 
who have registered themselves in the manner laid down by law, 
excepting persons who, since 21 August 1991, have obtained 
citizenship of another country -- that is, those who have 
obtained another country's citizenship since 21 August 1991 
[sentence as heard]. According to this bill, citizens are also 
persons who have been naturalized or who have otherwise obtained 
citizenship of the Republic of Latvia in the manner determined 
by law; foundlings and orphans living in Latvian children's 
homes or boarding schools, as well as children, both of whose 
parents were citizens of the Republic of Latvia at the moment of 
their birth, irrespective of the child's place of birth. The 
Saeima plenary session is still continuing. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

