<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Counterintelligence Chief Flies to Far East </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Counterintelligence Chief Flies to Far East </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306102594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1007 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1306102594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow June 13 TASS -- Director of the Federal 
Counterintelligence Service (FCIS) Sergey Stepashin flew to the 
Far East this Monday on a working trip, during which he will 
visit Vladivostok, Nakhodka and the Kurile Islands. 
  ITAR-TASS learnt at the FCIS that the director will meet 
population in the Far East, counterintelligence officers and 
will study the situation to map out measures to cut crime in the 
region and to realise the comprehensive crime-control programme. 

</TEXT>

