<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vietnamese Prime Minister Ends Official Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vietnamese Prime Minister Ends Official Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006163994 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1500 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1006163994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vo Van Kiet, prime minister of the Socialist 
Republic of Vietnam, today completed his official visit to 
Ukraine. During the visit he met Ukraine's President Leonid 
Kravchuk. The head of the Vietnamese Government also met Acting 
Prime Minister Yukhym Zvyahilskyy and Oleksandr Tkachenko, first 
deputy chairman of the Supreme Council of Ukraine. 
  A package of Ukrainian-Vietnamese agreements have been 
signed, in particular, a consular convention and 
intergovernmental agreements on attracting and protecting 
investments. A treaty on the principles of relations and 
cooperation between Ukraine and the Socialist Republic of 
Vietnam has been initialled. 
  The Vietnamese prime minister expressed the conviction that 
the arrival of the Vietnamese delegation in Kiev and the 
negotiations will initiate a new, important stage of cooperation 
on a direct interstate basis. 

</TEXT>

