<F P=106> [Unattributed report] </F>
  [Text] The newspaper ROSSIYSKIYE NOVOSTI published an 
interview with Crimean vice prime minister, Moscow economist 
Yevgeniy Saburov, in which he, in particular, characterizes the 
Crimean parliament. In his opinion, new voracious [holodni] 
people have come to power. They are not guided by the interests 
of voters, but by their own immediate interests. In Ye. 
Saburov's opinion, the way out of the deadlock lies in 
negotiations between the two sides that would rule out the use 
of force. He sees the Crimea's future "first and foremost, 
within Ukraine." 

</TEXT>

