<H3> <TI>   Interior Ministry Denies Civilian Casualties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Interior Ministry Denies Civilian Casualties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306140294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1152 
GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1306140294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 13 Jun -- The law enforcement agencies of 
the Chechen Republic this morning carried out an operation to 
localize and disarm the illegal gangs of bandits headed by 
Labazanov, Suleymanov, and Gantemirov. 
  The press service of Chechnya's Ministry of Internal Affairs 
told ITAR-TASS that the operation carried out by Interior 
Ministry forces, the Department of State Security and spetsnaz 
[special assignment] personnel of the republic's armed forces on 
the outskirts of Groznyy, ended at 1200 hours. According to the 
latest information, between 15 and 20 people were injured on 
both sides. The commander of a Chechen spetsnaz subunit was 
killed. 
  Suleymanov, one of the leaders of the bandit gangs, was 
arrested and taken to the hospital in a serious condition. The 
fate of Labazanov is not yet known. A search is continuing for 
others who fled the scene of the clash. 
  Chechnya's Ministry of Internal Affairs told ITAR-TASS that 
allegations by certain section of the media about armed clashes 
that are supposed to have taken place in Groznyy involving armor 
and civilian casualties are not true. 

</TEXT>

