<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Situation `Tense' Following Clashes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Situation `Tense' Following Clashes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406100494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0912 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1406100494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Grozny [Groznyy] June 14 ITAR-TASS--The situation 
remains tense in Chechnya, where several people were killed and 
injured on Monday in fighting between police and an armed group 
led by Ruslan Labazanov. The precise amount of victims from 
both sides has not been reported. Practically none of the 
political parties and movements in opposition to Dzhokhar 
Dudayev claimed responsibility for the clash. 
  The Labazanov group has been acting openly on the territory 
of Chechnya for nearly a year and declared in the official media 
its claims to be regarded as a political party. 
  The location of the leader of the group who managed to 
escape 
on Monday with several of his supporters has not been identified 
yet. The police admits the fact that he is now particularly 
dangerous as a source and instigator of terror. 
  Russia's plenipotentiary envoy Schmidt Zablayev is expected 
to arrive in Chechen capital on Tuesday where he will try to 
re-establish dialogue between Moscow and Grozny, but few people 
believe his mission will be effective. 

</TEXT>

