<H3> <TI>   Four Arrested in Attempt To Assassinate Dudayev </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Four Arrested in Attempt To Assassinate Dudayev </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1306134594 Moscow KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA in Russian 11 Jun 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM1306134594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report from the "Inform" column: "Dzhokhar </F>
Has No Enemies Any Longer"] 
  [Text] Four citizens of Chechnya suspected of an attempt 
on the life of President Dzhokhar Dudayev were arrested in 
Groznyy in the early hours of Thursday morning. As Sultan 
Geliskhanov, head of the Chechen State Security Department, 
informed INTERFAX, this group is suspected of preparing a series 
of attempted assassinations of a number of top officials of the 
republic. 
  Remote-controlled plastic explosive devices and firearms 
were 
seized from the arrestees, INTERFAX was informed at the State 
Security Department. 
  The attempted assassination of Dudayev occuurred on 27 May, 
when a Zhiguli packed with explosives parked by the side of the 
road was detonated as a convoy of vehicles, including the 
president, approached Groznyy. The internal affairs minister 
and his deputy were killed as a result. Dudayev himself was not 
hurt. 

</TEXT>

