<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ossetian Leader, Caucasus Official Discuss Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ossetian Leader, Caucasus Official Discuss Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306155594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1335 
GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1306155594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz, 13 Jun (ITAR-TASS) -- Issues relating 
to settling relations between North Ossetia and Ingushetia and 
the return of refugees to their previous residence were 
discussed at a meeting in Vladikavkaz today between Akhsarbek 
Galazov, president of North Ossetia, and Shmidt Dzoblayev, 
secretary general of the Assembly of Democratic Forces of the 
Northern Caucasus. The latter briefed Akhsarbek Galazov on his 
meeting in Nazran today with Ruslan Aushev, president of the 
Ingush republic, during which the issue of seeking a path to 
peace and accord in the region was discussed. 
  The leader of the movement proposed that a conference of the 
elders and religious authorities of the region on reconciliation 
should be held soon within the framework of stabilizing the 
situation in the conflict zone with the mediation of the 
Assembly of Democratic Forces of the Northern Caucasus. In his 
opinion, this would make it possible to create real 
prerequisites for implementing the 30th May decree of the 
Russian president "On Introducing a State of Emergency on Part 
of the Territories of the Republic of North Ossetia and the 
Ingush Republic." 
  The Assembly's secretary general also discussed with 
Akhsarbek Galazov the issue of relations with the Chechen 
republic, of involving its leader in the work of the commission 
to regulate Ossetia-Ingush relations and also of his plans 
connected with the forthcoming meeting with Dzhokhar Dudayev, 
leader of Chechnya. 
  Shmidt Dzoblayev said that Groznyy intends to examine 
relations between Chechnya and Russia, relating to regulating 
talks with its leadership and to the role of Chechnya in 
establishing law and order, peace, and calm in the region. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

