<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vietnam's Vo Van Kiet Meets Nazarbayev </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vietnam's Vo Van Kiet Meets Nazarbayev </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306182594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1312 
GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1306182594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by KAZTAG correspondent Ivan Zakharchenko and </F>
ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Kulagin] 
  [Text] Almaty, 13 June -- The two countries stand to 
mutually benefit most from cooperation between Kazakhstan and 
Vietnam in the sphere of agriculture, oil-extraction, mining, 
and textile industries. This was noted today during talks 
between Sergey Tereshchenko, the prime minister of Kazakhstan, 
and Vo Van Kiet, the prime minister of Vietnam, who is in Almaty 
on an official visit. Earlier in the day the Vietnamese prime 
minister was received by the President Nursultan Nazarbayev. 
  The talks stressed that getting bilateral trade between 
Vietnam and Kazakhstan going promises prompt results. 
  In the opinion of the head of government of Kazakhstan, when 
attracting foreign investors, both countries should take into 
account the interests of the third party. From his point of 
view, the creation of joint enterprises in both countries, the 
exchange of scientific potential and mutual assistance in 
training cadres in specialities in short supply would be of 
indubitable benefit. 
  For his part, the Vietnamese prime minister proposed to set 
up an intergovernment commission for economic cooperation, this 
was perceived with interest. 
  After the talks a joint intergovernment statement was 
signed. 
  Today Kazakhstan-Vietnamese consultations were held within 
the framework of the premier's visit at the local foreign 
ministry. The heads of the foreign political departments of 
both countries, namely Kanat Saudabayev and Nguyen Manh Cam, 
reached an accord on interaction in the Asian process, in 
particular, for the purpose of implementing the initiative of 
President Nursultan Nazarbayev on ensuring security on the 
continent. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-40047 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov114_i_94004" </HT>


<HEADER>
