<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pavlodar Deputies Issue Appeal on Social Matters </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pavlodar Deputies Issue Appeal on Social Matters </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406104294 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 0100 GMT 
14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1406104294 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pavlodar Oblast maslikhat deputies of the standing 
commission for social policy matters adopted an appeal to the 
Kazakh Supreme Council. It says the oblast inhabitants standard 
of living is decreasing, food and goods prices are rising 
unstably, and payments of wages and pension are not paid on 
time, especially for workers in education, medicine, and 
culture. It can be interpreted as a great violation of the 
Kazakh law on labor and pension, of which Kazakhstan has signed 
the human right declaration. Therefore, it demands the adoption 
of a decree by the Supreme Council on payment of wages, pension, 
and benefits. In case of delay in payment, the Supreme Council 
should also adopt a law to pay additionally for inflation. 

</TEXT>

