<F P=100> Kyrgyzstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Akayev Meets Local Administrators To Discuss Economy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Akayev Meets Local Administrators To Discuss Economy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406102994 Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network in 
Kyrgyz 2300 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1406102994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kyrgyz </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yesterday at the house of government President Askar 
Akayev met heads of oblast, rayon, and town administrations. 
They discussed economic problems and hardships on the way to 
the market. In particular, the report presented by Akayev spoke 
about the poorly thought-out mechanism of settling payments 
between the branches of industry and enterprises. This 
negatively affects production and brings about a stop to work in 
plants and factories. Special attention was paid by Akayev and 
those who spoke during the discussion to agricultural issues. 
It was noted that owing to a timely allocation of a soft loan 
by the government, the spring field works were done in time. 
The fodder procurement campaign also began timely and in an 
organized way. Preparation for harvesting is in progress. The 
participants of the meeting outlined a number of concrete 
measures to improve work of the industry and agriculture. 

</TEXT>

