<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chairman of Parliament Urges Peaceful End to War </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chairman of Parliament Urges Peaceful End to War </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306142194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1343 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1306142194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tigran Liloyan] </F>
  [Text] Yerevan June 13 TASS -- Azerbaijani parliament 
Chairman Rasul Guliyev called for peaceful settlement of the 
conflict with Armenia over the disputed enclave of 
Nagorno-Karabakh. 
  In an interview with Armenian television on Monday, Guliyev 
said that all occupied territories must be freed and the sides 
involved should begin negotiations in order to determine 
Nagorno-Karabakh's status. 
  Guliyev stressed the need to find ways of economic 
integration. "We are bound to live together. We must not fear 
each other or fight each other," Guliyev said. 
  He believes that as soon as normal economic relations are 
restored, "our people will forget the war in six months." 

</TEXT>

