<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aliyev, Grachev Discuss Conflict, Russia's Interests </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aliyev, Grachev Discuss Conflict, Russia's Interests </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1306204394 Baku TURAN in English 1658 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1306204394 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku, June 13 (TURAN): "The leadership of the 
republic sees the results of the meetings and talks with Russian 
Defense Minister, Pavel Grachev, as fruitful and useful", the 
State Advisor, Gabil Guseyinli, told TURAN. 
  The same source reports that on June 11 during the talks, 
the 
Azeri President and Russian Defense Minister discussed military 
cooperation within the framework of the Collective Security Pact. 
  Pavel Grachev spoke about the need for cooperation between 
military personnel of both countries and promised to contribute 
to the creation of the Azeri army. 
  Discussing the Armenian-Azerbaijani conflict, Pavel Grachev 
said that he recognizes the territorial integrity of Azerbaijan 
and considers Nagorno-Karabakh a part of it. During the talks, 
the Grachev wished that Baku take into account the strategic and 
military intersts of Russia in the region. The Azeri President 
said that Russia's military leadership should use its 
opportunities and authority to reach a peaceful and diplomatic 
settlement of the Armenian-Azerbaijani conflict and the 
liberation of all occupied- territories by the Armenians. 
Sources from the Presidential staff of Azerbaijan report that 
the introduction of the Russian peacemaking forces in the 
conflict region was not a major part of the discussion. 
However, Grachev and people close to him, repeatedly stated the 
necessity to introduce Russian peacemaking forces in the 
conflict region. 

</TEXT>

