<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Free' Use `Likely' for Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Free' Use `Likely' for Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406114194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1027 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1406114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia is likely to use the Gabalinskaya radar 
station free in exchange for concessions in other areas to 
Azerbaijan, where the station is situated. A reliable source in 
the administration of the Azeri president told Interfax about 
this preliminary understanding reached during Pavel Grachev's 
visit to Baku on June 11. 
  The source said that if the talks on the Gabalinskaya 
station 
are a success and interests of both sides are taken into 
account, the station will be operated only by Russian military 
personnel. 
  The source said that after an understanding is reached in 
principle, experts of Russia and Azerbaijan will draft the text 
of a document. 

</TEXT>

