<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Kozyrev Talks With Bosnia's Karadzic </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on Kozyrev Talks With Bosnia's Karadzic </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406101994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1002 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1406101994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Dmitriy Gorokhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 14 TASS -- Russian Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev opposed any unilateral steps in Bosnia and said 
the US intention to lift arms embargo against Bosnian Muslims 
can throw the world back to the times of the "Cold War". 
  "Russia will not resort to unilateral steps in its policy in 
the region which are not connected with the peaceful settlement 
and may destroy the basics of international peace and security. 
Such measures would be contrary to the Russian national 
interests, contrary to the basic interests of the people of 
Yugoslavia", he told Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic on 
Tuesday. 
  Kozyrev urged other countries to refrain from unilateral 
actions and expressed hope that the US Administration will not 
support the intention of the Congress to unilaterally lift the 
arms embagro on Bosnian Muslims. 
  "Otherwise a violation of the (UN) Security Council 
resolutions, the UN Charter will be evident which would create a 
new political situation. If any of the powers begins to 
unilaterally support those `under its wardship', the world will 
return to the worst times of the `Cold War'", he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

