<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Against Ending Sanctions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Against Ending Sanctions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406095594 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 
14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1406095594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev declared 
today that ending international sanctions against the Bosnian 
Muslims might return the world to a state of cold war and even 
push it into a third world war. He expressed his view to 
journalists, according to a REUTER report, after a meeting in 
Moscow with Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic, who has 
arrived in the Russian capital to receive a literary prize. 
  As is known, the other day the U.S. Congress decided on a 
unilateral dropping of the embargo on arms supplies to the 
Muslim side in the Bosnian conflict. The head of the Russian 
Foreign Ministry noted that Russia, for its part, will not be 
taking similar steps vis-a-vis the Bosnian Serbs unless they are 
connected with a peaceful settlement of the crisis. 

</TEXT>

