<H3> <TI>   Shumeyko: Chernomyrdin To Visit Bulgaria in Fall </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shumeyko: Chernomyrdin To Visit Bulgaria in Fall </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306121694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1147 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1306121694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Vladimir Abrosimov and Lyudmila </F>
Yermakova] 
  [Text] Sofia June 13 TASS -- Russia's Federation Council 
Speaker Vladimir Shumeyko, who is currently here on an official 
visit at the head of a Russian delegation, has announced that 
Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin is to visit Bulgaria 
in autumn. 
  Shumeyko said that during the forthcoming visit the Russian 
premier is expected to sign a package of documents that are of 
importance for the development of cooperation between the two 
countries. 
  This subject was also the focus of a meeting here on Monday 
between the Russian parliamentarians and Professor Lyuben Berov, 
chairman of Bulgaria's Council of Ministers. Special attention 
was devoted to matters connected with settling the two 
countries' mutual debts. 
  The two sides believe that it is now essential to approach 
this problem "in an unprejudiced way and find a mutually 
acceptable compromise", Shumeyko said. 
  Military-technical cooperation, including that between 
defence industry enterprises, was discussed as well. The two 
sides agreed that one should now renounce primitive forms of 
perestroyka-period cooperation, barter in particular, and move 
on to civilised forms acceptable throughout the world. 

</TEXT>

