<H3> <TI>   Russian, Ukrainian Space Experts Meet in Kharkov </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian, Ukrainian Space Experts Meet in Kharkov </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306175794 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1430 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1306175794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Video report by correspondent Vitaliy Pidchenko; from the </F>
"Novosti" newscast] 
  [Text] A meeting took place in Kharkov today that was 
attended by representatives of the leading space firms in Russia 
and Ukraine. 
  [Pidchenko] The participants in this meeting have been 
partners for quite some time. For more than 30 years they have 
worked in close contact, creating the country's strategic 
missile shield. Now, there is a state frontier between them, the 
enterprises, design bureaux, and institutes of the former 
Glavkosmos [USSR Main Administration for the Development and Use 
of Space Technology for the National Economy and Scientific 
Research]. Representatives of them arrived in Kharkov to 
discuss the future joint program. In particular, it is proposed 
that CIS nuclear power stations, as well as a number of main oil 
and gas pipelines, should be fitted with super-reliable systems 
of electronic control. 
  Within the framework of another program ordered by the 
Russian Central Bank, it is planned to create a global system of 
communications, putting three earth satellites into orbit. This 
will allow Russia and Ukraine, to begin with, and then other 
countries, to carry out interbank operations almost 
instantaneously. 

</TEXT>

