13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1306151294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Ostankino television company has reduced 
broadcasting to Armenia to just a few hours in the evenings. 
ITAR- TASS reports that this has been caused by demands for 
additional payments for daytime broadcasts. Tigran Akopyan, 
chairman of Armenia's State Television and Radio, explained that 
the restrictions will be in force until Yerevan pays Moscow for 
the additional expenses of communications enterprises. The 
technical service of Armenian television estimates the cost of 
the services at 600 million Russian rubles. 

