<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Vladimir Berezko under the "KRASNAYA ZVEZDA and </F>
News Agency Correspondents Report" rubric: "Strong `Barrier' to 
Smuggler Will Be Erected"] 
  [Text] Russian Federation Border Troops -- Colonel General 
Andrey Nikolayev, commander in chief of the Border Troops, 
indicated at a news conference: "Within the framework of 
Operation Putina [fishing] our state has shown that it has 
something to defend and the people to defend it with." 
  In addition to Putina in the Far East, as of 20 June the 
border guards together with interested departments are 
commencing Operation Zaslon [barrier] in the Sea of Azov, the 
Barents Sea, the White Sea, the Baltic, the Black Sea, the 
Caspian, on the Amur and Ussuri Rivers, and on Lake Peipus. 
Col. Gen. Andrey Nikolayev also reported that the killers of 
border guard officers in Tajikistan have been detained. 

