<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk Leaves for Luxembourg Talks, Accord Signing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk Leaves for Luxembourg Talks, Accord Signing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406081294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0746 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1406081294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko and </F>
Mikhail Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev June 14 TASS -- President of Ukraine Leonid 
Kravchuk left for Luxembourg today. His working visit is aimed 
at signing an agreement on partnership and cooperation between 
Ukraine and European communities. [as received] 
  Head of the Ukrainian presidential press service Viktor 
Stelmakh told ITAR-TASS that during his visit President Kravchuk 
will meet European Commission Chairman Jacque Delors, Grand Duke 
of Luxembourg Jean, Prime Minister Jacques Santer, speaker of 
the parliament Erna Hennicot-Schoepges and Vice-Premier Jacques 
Poos. 
  Ukrainian foreign minister and his Luxembourg counterpart 
are 
also expected to sign an agreement on air service between the 
two states. 

