<H3> <TI>   Talanchuk Pledges Agricultural Reform </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Talanchuk Pledges Agricultural Reform </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1206100194 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
0700 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1206100194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] It is necessary to create proper conditions for 
working people. As far as social protection is concerned, it 
should be provided to pensioners, children, invalids, and other 
sections of the population that need it. Presidential 
candidate, Ukraine's Minister of Education Petro Talanchuk was 
saying this while in Zhitomir. 
  He believes that it is necessary to carry out a wise policy 
of taxation and crediting, using all possible means so that 
people be paid properly for the work they do. Talanchuk pointed 
out that, if elected to the high post, he would, first and 
foremost, carry out transformations in the agro-industrial 
complex. According to the candidate, the countryside would 
provide Ukraine with ample quantities of food in two years time. 

</TEXT>

