<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Federal Assembly Decree on Commemorating WWII Victory </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Federal Assembly Decree on Commemorating WWII Victory </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1306143194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 11 Jun 94 
p 3 </F>

<F P=103> PM1306143194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Decree No. 123-I SF of the Federation Council of the </F>
Russian Federation Federal Assembly "On Preparations for the 
50th Anniversary of Victory in the Great Patriotic War," dated 
Moscow, 1 June 1994 and signed by V.N. Viktorov, deputy chairman 
of the Federation Council of the Russian Federation Federal 
Assembly] 
  [Text] Having listened to information submitted by the 
Federation Council Committee for Security and Defense Questions 
regarding preparations for the 50th anniversary of victory in 
the Great Patriotic War, the Federation Council decrees that: 
  1. The following proposals shall be submitted to the Russian 
Federation Government: 
  --funds shall be allocated from the federal budget to 
prepare 
and hold events in connection with celebrations to mark the 
memorial dates of the Great Patriotic War of 1941-1945; 
  --a set of measures to be organized and held in 1994-1995 
involving searching for and ceremonially reinterring the remains 
of soldiers who died during the Great Patriotic War on Russian 
territory and who were not given a proper burial is to be 
included in the work plan of the Russian Organizational 
Committee for Preparing and Holding Events in Connection With 
the Memorial Dates of the Great Patriotic War of 1941-1945. 
  2. Russian Federation representatives in the Russian 
Federation parliamentary delegation to the Interparliamentary 
Assembly of CIS Member States are to be tasked during 1994-1995 
with putting the issue of organizing and carrying out searches 
and ceremonial reinterments of the remains of soldiers who died 
during the Great Patriotic War on the territory of CIS member 
states and who were not given a proper burial onto the agenda of 
the next session of the Interparliamentary Assembly. 
  [Signed] V.N. Viktorov, deputy chairman of the Federation 
Council of the Russian Federation Federal Assembly 
  Moscow 
  1 June 1994 
  No. 123-I SF 

</TEXT>

