<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agreement Signed on CIS Envoys Rights in Minsk </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Agreement Signed on CIS Envoys Rights in Minsk </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306151194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1351 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1306151194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On Monday [13 June] in Minsk, the Prime Minister of 
Belarus Vyacheslav Kebich and the CIS Executive Secretary Ivan 
Korotchenya signed an agreement on the terms of operation of CIS 
coordinating bodies in Belarus. The document provides for a set 
of benefits and privileges to these bodies. 
  The CIS Executive Secretariat shall be freed of all national 
and local taxes and payments, except compulsory social security 
payments. Neither will it have to pay export or import taxes or 
customs duties. 
  Its staff is exempt of criminal, civic and administrative 
responsibility under Belarussian jurisdiction for all actions as 
well as written and orals statements in office. Staff members 
enjoy personal inviolability and are freed from examination, 
detention and arrest. They have the right to the inviolability 
of their correspondence and documents. All payments they 
receive from the secretariat are exempt of taxation, except for 
compulsory social security payments. 
  According to the agreement, the correspondence and archives 
of the secretariat and permanent representatives are inviolable. 
Official reports cannot be censored. The secretariat and 
permanent representatives have the right to use ciphers of 
courier mail and other special forms of communications. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

