<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Wins Election in Zugdidi </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Wins Election in Zugdidi </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306142794 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 1300 
GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1306142794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Elections to the Georgian parliament were held 
yesterday in the western Georgian rayons of Zugdidi, 
Tsalenjikha, and Chkhorotsku. Our correspondent reports that 
preliminary information suggests that in all three rayons the 
turnout was above 60 percent. Preliminary information also 
suggests that Zugdidi candidate [and Georgia's Prime Minister] 
Otar Patsatsia received 70 percent of the votes, Chkhorotsku 
candidate Avtandil Tkebuchava received about 50 percent, and 
Tsalenjikha candidate Valeri Chanturia received more than 51 
percent. The final results will be known later. 

</TEXT>

