<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chernomyrdin Undergoes Gall Bladder Surgery </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chernomyrdin Undergoes Gall Bladder Surgery </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406114594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1119 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1406114594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia's Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin was 
operated on at Moscow's Central Clinic last Friday to grind his 
gall stone by ultrasound. As Interfax has learned, the surgery 
was performed on recommendations by the German specialists who 
examined Chernomyrdin at the Mainz University Clinic last week. 
  The operation is reported to have gone well, and doctors say 
it will take the patient a few days to recuperate. A government 
spokesman has reported that Chernomyrdin is due to be back at 
work from a short leave on June 16. 
  As has been reported the premier is scheduled to travel to 
the U.S. later this month to attend a session of the 
Russian-American commission which he co-chairs with U.S. Vice 
President Albert Gore. On his way to the U.S., Chernomyrdin 
plans to stop over in Italy. 
  He underwent a similarly successful operation at a clinic 
last autumn. However, surgeons recommended that he be examined 
at a specialized clinic abroad. It was after that examination 
that repeated surgery was recommended. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

