<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   National Organization Demands Tougher Stance on Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Organization Demands Tougher Stance on Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306161994 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 1140 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1306161994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 13 Jun -- The all-Ukrainian political union 
"State Independence of Ukraine" [DSU] has made public a 
statement. In order to guarantee peace and calm Ukraine, 
particularly in Crimea, the DSU demanded the following from the 
Supreme Council, the president, and Ukraine's leading power 
structures: 

  -  To return the status of Ukrainian oblast to Crimea, 
dissolve the Supreme Council of Crimea, and abolish the 
institution of the Crimean president; 
  -  To confirm that movable 
assets (combat ships and auxiliary vessels) and the 
infrastructure of the shore provision (ship repair yards, firing 
ranges, airports, and so on) remain the property of Ukraine; 
  -  To 
demand the relocation of the Black Sea Fleet personnel, which 
did not take the oath of allegiance to Ukraine, beyond Ukraine's 
borders. 

  In the event that the Black Sea Fleet does not relocate its 
army beyond the borders of Ukraine, to consider the Russian 
military contingents as occupational forces, and to demand that 
Ukraine's Defense Ministry adopt all measures to renew Ukrainian 
authority in Crimea," reads the DSU statement. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

