<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Claims Elections `Violation' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Claims Elections `Violation' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1306200394 Yerevan SNARK in English 1330 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1306200394 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, June 13. (SNARK) -- By-elections to the 
Georgian Parliament, which took place on June 12, passed with 
gross violation of the Law on Elections. Such declaration was 
made today by Vice-speaker of the Georgian Parliament Vakhtang 
Rcheulishvili. He informed SNARK of the facts which put in 
question the legitimacy of the elections. The Chairman of one 
of the Electoral Commissions and his Assistant had to leave 
their places to save their lives. Serious collisions took place 
at some election districts, at two of them arms were used. The 
candidates began blaming each other in using military 
detachments to get additional votes. 
  Mr. Rcheulishvili said in the towns of Zugdidi, Chkhorotsku 
and Salendzhikha 60-65 per cent of all the voters took part in 
the elections, when in Rustavi - only 10 per cent. 
  "Presumably, the Central Electoral Committee will find 
illegal the results of the by-elections in the towns of Western 
Georgia", declared the Georgian Vice-speaker. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

