<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Three Parties Form `United Republican Party of Georgia' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Three Parties Form `United Republican Party of Georgia' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306192594 Tbilisi First Program Television Network in 
Georgian 1600 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1306192594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi First Program Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The leaders of the People's Front, Charter-91, 
and the Republican Party signed an agreement today uniting the 
three parties into a single political organization. The new 
organization will be called the United Republican Party of 
Georgia. [passage omitted] 
  The text of the agreement was presented to journalists and 
participants at the ceremony by chairman of the People's Front, 
Nodar Natadze. 
  The United Republican Party's manifesto was presented by the 
leader of Charter-91, Tedo Paatashvili. 
  The leader of the Republican Party, Vakhtang Gabiradze, read 
out the list of members of the new party's provisional ruling 
body, the Political Council. [passage omitted] 
  The United Republican Party will work as a single faction in 
the Georgian Parliament. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

