  [Excerpts] The Baltic Council of Ministers which was set up 
today should provide a firm basis for Baltic cooperation. Anne 
Osvet reports. 
  [Osvet] During the Baltic prime ministers' meeting in 
Tallinn 
today the foundations were laid, among other things, for yet 
another cooperation body. I asked for more clarification from 
Alar Olljum, deputy chancellor of the Estonian Foreign Ministry. 
  [Begin Olljum recording] As of today, the Baltic Council of 
Ministers has been set up. [passage omitted] The agreement 
which was signed today by the prime ministers of the Baltic 
