<H3> <TI>   Duma Speaker Shares Yeltsin Views on DPRK Sanctions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Duma Speaker Shares Yeltsin Views on DPRK Sanctions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406142194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1332 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1406142194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] State Duma Speaker Ivan Rybkin fully shares 
President Yeltsin's view that international sanctions against 
North Korea should be coordinated with UN members and imposed 
gradually. As the chairman of the State Duma Defense Committee, 
Sergey Yushenkov, told Interfax, Rybkin expressed this agreement 
with Yeltsin's view on Tuesday, when receiving a parliamentary 
delegation from Britain. 
  Led by the chairman of the Standing Commission for Defense 
of 
the House of Commons, Nicholas Bonsor, the delegation took part 
in Tuesday's round-table conference on collective security in 
Europe held at the lower chamber of Russia's parliament. 
  Interfax's correspondent reports that on Wednesday British 
MPs intend to visit Russia's Defense Ministry, Institute for 
Strategic Studies and a military unit. 
  Thursday evening they will leave for Kiev. 

