<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev, Christopher Discuss DPRK `Problem' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev, Christopher Discuss DPRK `Problem' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506014994 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0100 GMT 
15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1506014994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher and 
Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev had a telephone 
conversation on Tuesday. They discussed the North Korean 
problem and in particular, the status of North Korea following 
its official announcement that it resigns from the IAEA. Both 
sides agreed that the announcement had the most serious 
consequences and that the United States and Russia would 
continue to hold close consultations through their 
representatives in the United Nations. They also discussed the 
question of Russia joining the Partnership for Peace program. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

