<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Receives Bosnian Serb Leader Karadzic </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Receives Bosnian Serb Leader Karadzic </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406145794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1400 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1406145794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Dmitriy Gorokhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 14 TASS -- "Nobody knows how the recent 
crisis over Sarajevo would end if it were not for the initiative 
of President Boris Yeltsin", Radovan Karadzic said on Tuesday 
regarding Russia's support for Bosnian Serbs. At a meeting with 
Andrey Kozyrev in the Russian Foreign Ministry he said the 
Russian people had been Serbs friends over centuries. 
  Radovan Karadzic arrived in Moscow to receive a literary 
prize named after Mikhail Sholokhov that was awarded to him by 
the Russian Writers Union. Karadzic said he intends to meet 
representatives of various political trends. He said he will 
never forget priority role of the Russian Government and Russian 
diplomacy in the quest for peaceful solution to the Bosnian 
conflict. He said Bosnian Serbs are aware of Russia's 
objectivity so they believe it will not be biased in the 
approach to the events in the region. 
  "It is very difficult to end the civil war. Not only the 
armies but also civilians are involved in hostilities", Karadzic 
said. "We are sick and tired of the crisis lasting for several 
years. We need peace in order to build a democratic society and 
free economy". 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

