<H3> <TI>   Troops Begin Mine-Clearing Operations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Troops Begin Mine-Clearing Operations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506084994 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0800 GMT 
15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1506084994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Russian troops' peacekeeping operation in the 
zone of the Georgian-Abkhazian conflict has begun. As INTERFAX 
reports, this morning sappers of the Russian 345th Airborne 
Regiment started clearning mines from territory in Abkhazia's 
Galskiy [Gali] Rayon. 
  Colonel General Georgiy Kondratyev, Russian deputy defense 
minister who arrived in Sukhumi on Wednesday, said the direct 
introduction of Russian forces on the lines of contact of the 
combatant sides along the Inguri River will be effected in the 
perdiod from 16 to 21 June after the mines have been cleared 
from the territory. 
  He said the batallion of the 345th Airborne Regiment, which 
regiment is stationed at Gudauta, would act as disengagement 
forces at the initial stage. In this same period, Kondratyev 
noted, the combatant sides should start pulling back their armed 
formations 12 km from the river. 

</TEXT>

