<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin To Sign Partnership Agreement With EU </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin To Sign Partnership Agreement With EU </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406175894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1625 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1406175894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Minayev] </F>
  [Text] Luxembourg June 14 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin will sign an agreement on partnership and cooperation 
between Russia and the European Union on the Greek island of 
Corfu on June 24, Greek Deputy Foreign Minister Theodhoros 
Pangalos [title as received] said on Tuesday. 
  According to the diplomat, who chaired the two-day sitting 
of 
the EU Council of Foreign Ministers in Luxembourg, after that, 
leaders of Austria, Norway, Finland and Sweden will sign a 
treaty on their counries' joining the European Union. A day 
before the ceremonies, Yeltsin and heads of member-countries of 
the EU will discuss pressing international problems at a working 
dinner. 
  According to Pangalos, the text of the Russian-EU agreement 
has been discussed by the ministers. During the next few days 
the amendments concerning the activities of five foreign banks 
on the Russian territory will be introduced in the agreement by 
the EU's Committee of Permanent Representatives. 

</TEXT>

