<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Dmitriy Gorokhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 14 TASS -- A Russian Foreign Ministry's 
official said Russia is likely to join the European Council in a 
few months. 
  "We presume that Russia might become a member of the 
European 
Council within the next six months, and not later than next 
spring", Galina Sidorova, a spokeswoman for Russian Foreign 
Minister Andrey Kozyrev, told reporters on Tuesday. 
  According to Sidorova, earlier, Russia's entering the EC was 
conditioned on the adoption of a new constitution. 
  Now Russia has its new constitution adopted. And this 
"enables her to bid for an equal place among the members of the 
European Council", she said. 

