<H3> <TI>   Duma Official, UK Official Discuss DPRK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Duma Official, UK Official Discuss DPRK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506055994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0541 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506055994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 15 TASS -- "It's for the first time that 
the world encounters such outrageous nuclear blackmail as in 
North Korea's case," said chairman of the Duma Committee for 
Defence, Sergey Yushenkov, when he met his British counterpart, 
Chairman of the Permanent Committee for Defence Nicholas Bonser, 
"Ekho Moskvy" radio reported on Tuesday night. 
  Commenting on North Korea's problem, Bonser pointed out that 
the most important thing in this crisis was to show firm 
determination so that other countries would not be tempted to 
follow North Korea's example. Otherwise, a potential threat of 
a nuclear conflict might appear for the first time after the 
Second World War, the British lawmaker said. 
  Yushenkov pointed out that the "Partnership for Peace" 
programme can play an important role in the prevention of 
conflicts similar to the Yugoslav and Korean crises. 

</TEXT>

