<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   IAEA Experts Inspect Kola Nuclear Power Station </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IAEA Experts Inspect Kola Nuclear Power Station </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506090394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0845 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506090394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Murmansk June 15 TASS--The nuclear power station on 
the Kola peninsula can operate until its design service life 
expires, says a conclusion made by an IAEA commission which has 
just ended its inspection of the station. 
  The commission checked whether recommendations given to the 
personnel of the station by IAEA experts two years ago had been 
followed. It was recommended then to enhance the reliability of 
the safety systems of the first and second nuclear reactors and 
replace outdated equipment by a modern one. The IAEA inspection 
pointed out that half of these recommendations had been already 
fulfilled. 

</TEXT>

