<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy May Be Charged for Inciting `War Propaganda' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhirinovskiy May Be Charged for Inciting `War Propaganda' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406135894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1325 
GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1406135894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Olga Solodova for CRIME-PRESS] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 14 Jun -- Aleksey Ilyushenko, the acting 
procurator-general of the Russian Federation, has made an 
application to the State Duma requesting that it consent to 
criminal prosecution being brought against Federal Assembly 
deputy Vladimir Zhirinovskiy for war propaganda (Article 71 of 
the Russian Criminal Code) and for inciting ethnic hostility and 
tension (Article 74 of the Russian Criminal Code). 
  The information and public relations center of the Russian 
Procuracy General stated that the conclusions of a preliminary 
investigation which is now being conducted by the Russian 
Procuracy General into a criminal case instituted on 26 January 
of this year in connection with the publication and distribution 
of Vladimir Zhirinovskiy's book "The Last Thrust to the South" 
formed the grounds for this application. 

</TEXT>

