<H3> <TI>   Zatulin Resigns From PRES Faction Post </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zatulin Resigns From PRES Faction Post </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506080994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0645 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506080994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Ivanova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 15 TASS -- The parliamentary faction of 
the Party of Russian Unity and Accord [PRES] accepted the 
resignation of Konstantin Zatulin as the faction's secretary in 
the State Duma, the press service of the lower house of the 
Russian parliament reported today without divulging the reasons 
for the resignation. 
  Zatulin retains the post of the chairman of the State Duma 
Committee for Commonwealth Affairs and Relations with 
compatriots abroad. 
  Vladimir Kozhemiakin, who headed Sergey Shakhray secretariat 
before his election to the State Duma, will replace Zatulin as 
secretary of the PRES faction in parliament. 

