<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military, Nuclear &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Antiterrorist Border Guard Unit To Be Formed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Antiterrorist Border Guard Unit To Be Formed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK1506070094 Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS in Russian 15 Jun 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK1506070094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Border Guards Acquire Their Own </F>
`Alfa'"] 
  [Text] As MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS has learned, recently yet 
another antiterrorist unit has been created in Russia. Now the 
task of freeing hostages captured on the border will be handled 
by specially trained border guard groups. 
  There will be no conscripts serving in this special task 
force. At present work is under way to select graduates from 
border guard schools and reenlisted men for this unit. 
Antiterrorist groups will not be very large: 15 to 20 people. 
So far it is planned to create five groups based in different 
regions of Russian, as a rule near the state border. They will 
be geared toward securing the release of hostages taken on the 
country's territory and taken abroad; that is to say, actions on 
the territory of other states. The special force will be used 
primarily to free Russian servicemen, including border guards. 
The decision to use the special unit will be made at a level 
not below Russian border guards commander. 
  According to some reports, these groups will be trained by 
the Alfa force and its regional subdivisions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

