<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military, Nuclear &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Closing Chernobyl To Benefit Foreign Companies </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Closing Chernobyl To Benefit Foreign Companies </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406145394 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 15 Jun 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> LD1406145394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report from ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA-ITAR-TASS column: </F>
"Beneficial to Foreign Companies"] 
  [Text] The question of the possible closure of the 
Chernobyl Nuclear Electric Power Station has been discussed 
increasingly often recently by the world community, not only at 
an environmental and social level but also at a political level. 
  Circles close to the Russian Federation Ministry of Atomic 
Energy have stated that if such a step is taken it will have 
primarily political overtones. In the opinion of the experts, 
this will be beneficial first and foremost to the leading 
foreign nuclear power generation companies. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

