<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Arrives in Blagoveshchensk; Tours Amur Oblast </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Arrives in Blagoveshchensk; Tours Amur Oblast </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Concerned About Dependence on Subsidies </H4>

<F P=102> LD1406133794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1305 
GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1406133794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Zamyatina] </F>
  [Text] Blagoveshchensk [center of Amur Oblast], 14 Jun -- 
Boris Yeltsin is concerned that a region of such rich natural 
potential as Amur Oblast should be living off subsidies from the 
federal budget. The Russian president stated this today on his 
arrival in Blagoveshchensk. 
  Replying to a question from an ITAR-TASS correspondent, 
Boris 
Yeltsin said that the Amur Oblast administration chief had 
visited him recently and they had put their heads together over 
how to revitalize the region. The president said that one of 
the aims of his trip to Amur Oblast and the Tuva Republic was to 
study the potential of these regions with a view to identifying 
measures to help extricate their economies from crisis. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

