<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia, Bashkorstan Treaty To Be Drafted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia, Bashkorstan Treaty To Be Drafted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506103294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1007 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506103294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow June 15 ITAR-TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin today set up a commission to prepare a bilateral treaty 
between the Russian Federation and one of its constituent parts, 
the Republic of Bashkortostan. The treaty is due to divide 
powers between the federation and its component republic and 
decide on the delegation of powers between the bodies of state 
authorities of Russia and Bashkortostan, the presidential press 
service announced today. 
  Vice-Premier Sergey Shakhray is appointed to head the 
commission. 
  Earlier, Moscow signed a treaty with Tatarstan, another 
component republic of the Russian Federation. 

</TEXT>

