<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   CSCE-Initiated Caucasus Meeting Held </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CSCE-Initiated Caucasus Meeting Held </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406201094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1400 
GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1406201094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz, 14 Jun -- The latest meeting of 
delegations from Georgia, South and North Ossetia, and 
representatives of the CSCE, aimed at continuing the search for 
peace and reconciliation, which began after the dialogue on 12 
May, took place in Vladikavkaz today on the initiative of the 
CSCE mission in Georgia. 
  The parties agreed in particular on the need to carry out 
joint work to stabilize the situation in the conflict zone, to 
fight organized crime, to restore road and rail traffic between 
Tskhinvali and other towns, to begin cooperating on economic 
revival, and to restore housing and the appropriate 
infrastructure. 
  The meeting participants agreed to help keep peace and law 
and order in the conflict zone by means of observation by the 
CSCE mission. There are proposals for the practical and legal 
basis to be created jointly for the speedy return of refugees 
and for an appeal to be made to the peacekeeping forces for the 
preparation of the necessary conditions to guarantee the 
refugees safety and also for enlisting the support of the UN 
High Commissioner for Refugee Affairs. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

