<F P=106> [Report attributed to the Belarusian Defense Ministry press </F>
center] 
  [Text] As part of a military and technical cooperation 
plan for the Defense Ministries of Belarus and Poland, a 
delegation from the Management and Development Administration of 
the Polish Defense Ministry, headed by its deputy chief Jan 
Fedoruski, has paid a visit to Minsk. 
  During negotiations with Colonel Vasiliy Pugachev, chairman 
of the Scientific and Technical Committee at the Belarusian 
Defense Ministry, problems related to prospective technical 
equipment for both states' Armed Forces were discussed. The 
sides conveyed their experiences in developing military science 
and examined issues concerning joint scientific research and 
design projects. 
  The Polish military delegation visited the Belarusian 
Optical 
Amalgamation, the Means of Automation Scientific Research 
Institute, and the Minsk Tractor Plant. 

