<H3> <TI>   Snegur Denies Stalling Dniester Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Snegur Denies Stalling Dniester Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406104094 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1000 GMT 
14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1406104094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Mircea Snegur today denied an allegation 
by Tiraspol authorities that the Moldovan leadership is blocking 
the continuation of talks started under Russian and CSCE 
mediation on the peaceful settlement of the Dniester conflict. 
  As already reported, Igor Smirnov, leader of the Dniester 
region, accused Chisinau last week of silently blocking the 
dialogue to settle the crisis. He appealed to Vladlen Vlasov, 
the Russian president's special envoy at the talks, requesting 
that the latter use his influence over Snegur who, in Tiraspol's 
view, is avoiding talks. 
  A statement issued today by an official representative of 
the 
president of Moldova says that the Republic's leadership has set 
up a group of experts to draft a bill on the special juridical 
status of the region on the left bank of the Dniester River. It 
has been ready to begin work for a long time, but Tiraspol is 
delaying setting up a similar group for joint work on the bill, 
as agreed during the meeting held at the end of April between 
the leaders of Moldova and the Dniester region. 

</TEXT>

