<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Army Commander Calls Tiraspol Leaders `Swindlers' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Army Commander Calls Tiraspol Leaders `Swindlers' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1406160094 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2244 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1406160094 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tiraspol BASAPRESS, 10/6/1994 -- A meeting of the 
Union of Veterans of the Afghanistan War was held yesterday in 
Tiraspol. The meeting was attended by representatives of the 
Afghanistan war veterans' unions of Moldova, Ukraine, and 
Russia. The participants criticized the Tiraspol authorities 
for leaving the veterans and the families of Afghanistan war 
victims without social protection. Aleksandr Karaman, the vice 
president of the self-proclaimed Dniester Republic declared at 
the meeting that due to a very severe economic situation, when 
internal production has fallen by 26 percent, the leadership of 
Tiraspol is forced to make cuts in some social assistance 
programs. Aleksandr Lebed, the commander of the 14th Russian 
Army [currently stationed in Dniester], who also took the floor, 
declared that the leadership of Dniester is made up of swindlers 
who pretend that certain social organizations, including the 
Union of Afghanistan War Veterans, are taking an active part in 
the political life -- especially in the future elections to the 
leadership [sentence as received]. The meeting adopted a 
declaration which announces its intention to take part actively 
in the political life and future elections. 

</TEXT>

