<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   SHAPE Chief Leads NATO Delegation Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SHAPE Chief Leads NATO Delegation Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506092594 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 1400 GMT 
14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1506092594 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, at the house of parliament, the NATO 
delegation led by General Peter Heinrich Carstens, chief of 
staff of Supreme Headquarters Allied Powers Europe [SHAPE], was 
received. In the conversation that took place, deputy speaker 
Kuanysh Sultanov told the guest that Kazakhstan's new foreign 
policy is based on that of a non-nuclear country. The 
parliament, he stressed, endorsed the fundamentals of the 
defense doctrine. Much attention is paid to building and 
developing the armed forces. He expressed hope for the 
possibility of cooperation with all NATO member states for the 
sake of preserving peace and good relations. 
  The general spoke about the concept of the Partnership for 
Peace program and its future development. He expressed 
satisfaction that three Central Asian states, including 
Kazakhstan, signed the document on cooperation in the framework 
of their program. At its early stage, establishment of 
political contacts is envisaged. In September, the first joint 
military training exercise will take place, and observers from 
Kazakhstan are invited to participate. 

</TEXT>

