<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Industrial Output in Semipalatinsk Declines 30 Percent </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Industrial Output in Semipalatinsk Declines 30 Percent </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506124294 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 0100 GMT 
15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1506124294 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This year, under various pretexts, over 60 
industrial enterprises in Semipalatinsk Oblast have come to a 
standstill. Over 20,000 workers have lost their jobs. In 
addition, small businesses, with a total work force of over 
3,500 workers, have also discontinued work. Over 20 other 
enterprises of the oblast, which employ a total of about 6,500 
people, are working half days. The oblast's industrial output 
has declined by 30 percent, as compared with last year. 

</TEXT>

