Daily Report 
<DATE1>  14 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Welcomes Signing of Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Welcomes Signing of Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406190094 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1600 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1406190094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The signature of the agreement on partnership 
and cooperation between Ukraine and the European Union took 
place in Luxembourg on 14 June. This was an announcement made 
at a briefing at Ukraine's Foreign Affairs Ministry. [passage 
omitted] 
  Speaking at the ceremony of signing the document, Ukrainian 
President Leonid Kravchuk said the agreement was laying a 
qualitatively new legal foundation of our state's inclusion in 
European integrational processes. As well as being a matter of 
fundamental priority, he underlined, Ukraine's accession to 
European economic and political structures is a logical and 
necessary course of its external policy at the present stage. 
  The Ukrainian president added that the single Europe would 
also benefit a lot from cooperation with Ukraine in terms of the 
availability of transit roads across the territory of Ukraine, 
rich deposits of raw materials, and tens of millions of highly 
skilled workers. 
  If the boat of the Ukrainian state is rocked loose, Kravchuk 
warned, it can become a potential source of instability on the 
continent. 

</TEXT>

