  [Text] The second round of Tajikistan's peace talks will 
commence on 18 June in Tehran. 
  The office of the UN secretary general announced that the 
talks, which are aimed at achieving national reconciliation in 
Tajikistan, will be chaired by Ramero Piriz Ballon, an envoy of 
the secretary general. 
  In addition to Tajik Government authorities and the 
government opposition groups, the representatives of the Islamic 
Republic of Iran, Russia, Pakistan, Afghanistan, Kazakhstan, 
Kyrgystan, Uzbekistan, and CSCE will attend the talks. 

