<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Officer Killed in Khatlon Region </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Officer Killed in Khatlon Region </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506051994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0454 
GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1506051994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe, 15 Jun -- Mikhail Osipov, commander of the 
191st company of the 201st Motorized Infantry Regiment of the 
collective peacekeeping forces, was killed on Tuesday [14 June] 
in the Tajik town of Kurgan-Tyube (the administrative centre of 
Khatlon region). ITAR-TASS learned at the press centre of the 
joint command of the collective peacekeeping forces that the 
30-year-old lieutenant was shot at about 23 hours local time 
(2200 hours Moscow time) from an automatic weapon by 
unidentified persons while checking on a street patrol. The 
motives of the murder are being established. An investigation 
into the circumstances of the crime has begun. 

</TEXT>

