<F P=100> Kyrgyzstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   President, Prime Minister Dismiss Rayon Chiefs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President, Prime Minister Dismiss Rayon Chiefs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506105294 Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network in 
Russian 2300 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1506105294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Dzhumagulov signed a resolution "On 
dismissing the heads of rayon state administrations" in 
accordance with which Torebekov Orozbek is relieved of his post 
as head of the Karabura rayon state administration of Talas 
oblast for shortcomings in his work and lack of exactingness to 
the personnel and for the economic situation in his rayon; 
Sisenov Dzolboldy is relieved of the post of head of the Suzak 
rayon state administration of Dzhelalabad oblast for serious 
shortcomings in implementing the land and agrarian reforms; 
Bekishev Bekbola is dismissed from the post of head of the 
Uchterek rayon state administration of Dzhelalabad oblast for 
discrediting the idea of land and agrarian reform which was 
expressed in many complaints about his incompetent approach to 
the creation of a pluralistic economic structure in the rural 
area. 
  These resolutions of the government were submitted to the 
president of the Kyrgyz Republic for confirmation. President 
Akayev issued an order confirming the prime minister's 
resolution. 

</TEXT>

