<F P=100> Kyrgyzstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Debts to Uzbekistan for Natural Gas May Interrupt Supplies </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Debts to Uzbekistan for Natural Gas May Interrupt Supplies </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406130394 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1100 GMT 
14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1406130394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] There is a natural gas problem in Kyrgyzstan again. 
RIA was told by the government's press service that debt for 
gas to neighboring Uzbekistan currently amounts to approximately 
10 million U.S. dollars. The lion's share of that sum consists 
of the debts of the Republic's industrial sector due to its 
insolvency. The government and local administrations are also 
unable to subsidize gas consumption for the private sector. 
Kyrgyz authorities have been instructed to review gas charges 
with a view toward raising them, as a solution to a situation in 
which Uzbekistan may, at any moment, turn off the tap of natural 
gas supplies. 

</TEXT>

