<F P=101> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Political Parties Condemn Aliyev Headquarters Attack </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Political Parties Condemn Aliyev Headquarters Attack </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1406200894 Baku TURAN in English 1704 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1406200894 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku, June 14 (TURAN) -- The press service of 
Azerbaijan's Ministry of Internal Affairs issued a statement 
regarding the explosion in the headquarters of the Yeni 
Azerbaycan [New Azerbaijan] party and called it "open political 
terror". 
  The Ministry of Internal Affairs said that it will take 
drastic measures against those who are trying to destabilize the 
situation in the country. 
  The assault on the headquarters of the Yeni Azerbaycan 
party, 
whose Chairman is President Aliyev, took place on June 12 at 
night when the building was empty. The building was fired at 
from machine guns and then there was explosion inside. 
  Several parties, including the opposition parties of the 
Musavat, Azerbaijan Democratic Party and the Popular [People's] 
Front issued a statement in which they condemned this act of 
terrorism at the headquarters of Yeni Azerbaycan. The parties 
expressed concern about the fact that such acts against 
political parties are taking place with alarming frequency. 
  The opposition parties demanded the creation of normal 
conditions for the activities of all parties in keeping with the 
Constitution of the Republic of Azerbaijan. 

</TEXT>

