<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   `New Wave Association' Backs Kravchuk for President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `New Wave Association' Backs Kravchuk for President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406163094 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1520 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1406163094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lvov -- The political council of the New Wave 
Association has made its decision on support of candidates in 
the presidential election, Yuriy Shveda, chairman of the 
association's secretariat, told UNIAN on 14 June. "Only recently 
New Wave was inclined to support Ivan Plyushch," he said. "But 
today there are two presidential candidates who really stand a 
chance to be elected, Leonid Kuchma and Leonid Kravchuk. 
Considering this setup, and also the fact that Kuchma 
represents pro-Russian forces in Ukraine, New Wave has decided 
to support and campaign for the current president of Ukraine, 
Leonid Kravchuk. 
  "Although we have certain reservations about him, and we are 
particularly dissatisfied with his indecisive attitude to 
economic reforms and his personnel policy, New Wave sees no 
alternative to Kravchuk," Shveda told UNIAN. 

</TEXT>

