<H3> <TI>   Ukrainian Navy Shipyard To Be Set Up in Odessa </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ukrainian Navy Shipyard To Be Set Up in Odessa </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406161994 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1520 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1406161994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Odessa [no dateline as received] -- Warships that 
have been mothballed here for two years will soon undergo repair 
at a specialized Ukrainian Navy shipyard, which is being set up 
in cooperation with Odessa enterprise No. 108 and other 
specialized enterprises, Ukraine's navy commander Vice-Admiral 
Volodymyr Bezkorovaynyy told UNIAN on 14 June. He added that the 
Ukrainian Navy command had cancelled a contract with the 
commercial company FTF [as received] for the repair and 
replacement of equipment at the large assault-landing vessel 
"Ilya Azarov" and other ships. 
  "We are planning to use the renovated ships to improve the 
combat readiness of fleet units rather than for holiday cruises 
in the Mediterranean," Bezkorovaynyy said. 

</TEXT>

