<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin To Sign New Privatization Decree </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin To Sign New Privatization Decree </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506043594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0420 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506043594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondents Tamara Zamyatina and </F>
Vladimir Konoplitsky] 
  [Text] Blagoveshchensk June 15 TASS -- President Boris 
Yeltsin is expected to sign a decree soon on a new phase of 
privatisation, Presidential Press Secretary Vyacheslav Kostikov 
told journalists on Wednesday. 
  Yeltsin is to apply to the Federal Assembly and initiate a 
bill on a new phase of cheque privatisation which will meet both 
the interests of the country and those of regions and large 
cities. 
  This step by the president, in the opinion of the press 
secretary, develops and furthers the privatisation ideology 
worked out by the State Property Committee, and clearly 
differentates between federal, municipal and private property. 
Thus, the very dispute about privatisation methods at various 
levels will be politically settled. 
  Tackling this problem, the president proceeds from the 
assumption that under privatisation conditions, it is federal 
property interests first of all that must be upheld. No 
personnel reshuffles at the State Property Committee are 
expected. So, Anatoliy Chubays and Moscow Mayor Yuriy Luzhkov 
will have nothing to argue about any longer, Kostikov said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

